name: Nonie's
location_string: Boracay, Malay, Aklan Province, Panay Island, Visayas
description: At Nonie’s, we are believers in the slow food movement and the philosophy that everyone has the right to good, clean and fair food. This is what we aim to achieve through bringing our processing in house, baking our bread daily, making all our sauces and marinades from scratch, and using only the freshest ingredients possible. We also take our sourcing very seriously by working with family owned farms, so that we can trust where our food is coming from and to ensure we are directly impacting the community we live in. We aim to ensure our fresh produce and livestock are raised and harvested in an ethical and sustainable manner by building relationships with local farmers and visiting the source to really understand where our ingredients come from. We source within the Philippines and specifically within the Visayas region as much as possible, which allow us to reduce our carbon emissions. Our partners outside of this region are verified as either a sustainable, organic or natural source. We hope you enjoy our seasonal menu which our chefs work to curate to highlight the beauty of fresh Filipino ingredients. If you do have any food allergies or preferences, please do mention it to your server, who will be more than happy to recommend something suitable for you on our menu. Enjoy your visit to nonie’s and we look forward to seeing you soon.
